<aside id="name_filter_explanation">
  A regular expression that matches all the device hostnames in the site.  
  <br /><br />
  Omit the opening and closing slashes (/). When used, the name filter will be wrapped like this:
  <br /><br />
  /^name_filter$/i
  <br /><br />
  Examples:
  <ul>
    <li>AAS-\S+</li>
    <li>BCC-(TC|PC|ZC|MAC)-\d{2}</li>
    <li>ELLIS(114)?-(TC|ZC|MAC)-\d+</li>
  </ul>
  <br />
  For help with determining the correct regular expression, check out <a href="http://rubular.com" target="_blank">rubular.com</a>.
</aside>
